<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-02-01T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-02-01T21:00:00-05:00" n="242" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d242">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">352.115 Eastern States Petroleum Co./46:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi></persName>), <hi rend="italic">Then in
                            France</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-02-01T21:00:00-05:00">February 1, 1938—9
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>B–408. Reference Fisher’s report of 31st through Consulate at Gibraltar.
                            We are assuming that the indication of intention to release ship and
                            crew is true and will be carried out immediately. Please keep in touch
                            with Franco representative and advise us of all developments in this
                            connection. You should also make further urgent representations with a
                            view to effecting immediate release of captain.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>